  "title": "fix(searchBox): make svgs inherit color",
  "body": "**What project are you opening a pull request for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch (use v2 base)\r\n\r\n**Summary**\r\n\r\nright now you'd have to find a way to give the svg a fill (`.ais-SearchBox__reset svg, .ais-SearchBox__button svg { fill: red }`), but in most cases I imagine that in most cases, it should just be the same as whatever the current color is.\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nYou can style the searchbox with `.ais-SearchBox__reset, .ais-SearchBox__button { color: red }`, or `.ais-SearchBox { color: red }`, as well as other combinations. \r\n\r\nHowever this means that explicitly setting the fill might need a higher specificity (we will see when the deploy preview is done if this breaks our default theme, if it does some extra thought needs to be put in this PR)\r\n\r\ncc @Shipow for reasoning if this makes sense",
